# 60-Second Revision

- Bitwise operators work directly on binary bits.
- AND (`&`) returns 1 only if both bits are 1.
- XOR (`^`) returns 1 only if the bits are different.
- HashMap uses XOR for hash spreading.
- HashMap uses AND to calculate bucket indexes.
- `&` is faster than `%` because capacity is always a power of 2.
- Together, XOR and AND reduce collisions and improve HashMap performance.

